pageContext.claim: “Same with NATO. We're at 4 percent, and other countries are at 1 percent. And certainly, a European country benefits much more than we do with NATO. I mean, it's there for a reason. And perhaps we benefit, but not nearly as much as the European countries. Some people say we don't benefit at all.”
pageContext.analysis: The United States obviously benefits greatly from its association with NATO, both in terms of frontline projection of power and also in terms of maintaining alliances.
